# Components cheat-sheet

Fast reference for "what component handles this use case." Agent + human uses this first before reaching for custom composition.

## Actions

| Use case | Component | Import |
|---|---|---|
| Primary action | `<Button variant="primary">` | {{@/components/ui/button}} |
| Secondary action | `<Button variant="secondary">` | {{...}} |
| Destructive action | `<Button variant="destructive">` | {{...}} |
| Icon-only action | `<IconButton>` | {{...}} |

## Inputs

| Use case | Component | Import |
|---|---|---|
| Text input | `<Input>` | {{...}} |
| Textarea | `<Textarea>` | {{...}} |
| Select | `<Select>` | {{...}} |
| Checkbox | `<Checkbox>` | {{...}} |
| Radio | `<RadioGroup>` | {{...}} |

## Feedback

| Use case | Component | Import |
|---|---|---|
| Success / error toast | `<Toast>` | {{...}} |
| Inline validation | `<FormField>` + error state | {{...}} |
| Empty state | `<EmptyState>` | {{...}} |
| Loading | `<Skeleton>` | {{...}} |

## Layout

| Use case | Component | Import |
|---|---|---|
| Card surface | `<Card>` | {{...}} |
| Modal dialog | `<Dialog>` | {{...}} |
| Side sheet | `<Sheet>` | {{...}} |
| Tooltip | `<Tooltip>` | {{...}} |

## When to compose vs add a new primitive

- **Compose** when the use case is a combination of existing primitives (e.g., a card with a button = `<Card>` + `<Button>`)
- **Add a new primitive** only when (a) the composition would recur 3+ times, (b) there's clear semantic meaning, (c) an RFC has been reviewed — see [`../../docs/rubrics/component-budget.md`](../../docs/rubrics/component-budget.md) if present.
